race.description: Kirsty's Celebration 40 Years In The Making Hcp
race.comment: PLANET CASH (5) steps out to the mile again today, but importantly drops right back in grade. He's been contesting Saturday company recently and now lands in a CL5 on a Thursday. Likely to get back from the draw, but he was around the mark early in his campaign. A return to that level will see him hard to hold out. KIMBERLEY ROSE (4) finished off well first-up at Bunbury and stepping up in distance is a big tick for her. Steve Parnham replaces the apprentice hoop and with improvement likely, she appears the main danger. FIFTH ESSENCE (2) hasn't been far away in both runs this campaign, just missing at Pinjarra in this grade last start. The outside barrier is the query, but if he gets some luck he has the figures to be in the finish. LIEN HYPHEN (10) finished off strongly first-up and can build on that effort. THREE GRAND (9) is out in trip for the first time today and can improve.
